    "body": "I stumbled on this issue that xfsprogs currently does not install with error message:\r\n\r\n```\r\nFATAL ERROR: could not find a valid ini.h header.\r\n```\r\n:warning: :warning: :warning: \r\n\r\n(The warnings I added for greater effect :laughing: \r\n\r\nAnyway, adding this package libinih, and including it as a dependency for xfsprogs seems to fix the issue. \r\n\r\n## For Discussion\r\n\r\n- It looks like libinih doesn't have .tar.gz releases so I only added the master branch (it failed to install from the archive url that is under releases) so we might need to discuss that.\r\n- It could be that we only need to add it for newer versions (if it worked before) and maybe a maintainer can comment on that.\r\n\r\nSigned-off-by: vsoch <vsoch@users.noreply.github.com>",
